outputs.output_descr:
The present project represents second phase of the project 'Economic Development in the Adjara Autonomous Republic' implemented by UNDP in partnership with the Government of Romania and the Government of Adjara since January 2008. 
The overall objective of the project is to contribute to poverty reduction by promoting sustainable development in the Autonomous Republic of Adjara. A combination of economic development tools (business information centre, business incubator, LED strategy, vocational training, etc.) will be employed to enhance the region's ability to become both better governed and more economically diversified, thus counteracting poverty in the area.
